Will Rogers, Jr. tames the Old West with a rope and a grin as he brings law and order to a rowdy frontier town in this lighthearted adventure directed by Michael Curtiz.

The Boy from Oklahoma isn't a rollicking comedy. It is, however, a nicely crafted Western that is worth seeking out. Warner Bros. later adapted the film for the TV series Sugarfoot, which ran for four seasons in 1957-61. 

This obscure Western is great fun.
